'''Joy Banerjee''' (born 23 May 1960) is an [[India]]n actor known for his work in [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengali Cinema]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/people/joy-bandyopadhyay-131664|title=Joy Bandyopadhyay movies, filmography, biography and songs - Cinestaan.com|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2019-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gomolo.com/about-joy-bandyopadhyay/542|title=Joy Bandyopadhyay|website=gomolo.com|access-date=2019-03-28}}</ref>

He made his acting debut opposite [[Debashree Roy]] in ''Aparupa'' (1982) directed by Bidesh Sarkar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gomolo.com/aparupa-movie/14414|title=Aparupa (1982)|website=gomolo.com|access-date=2019-03-28}}</ref> He was critically applauded for his role in ''Chopper'' (1987) directed by [[Nabyendu Chatterjee]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/movies/chopper-34082|title=Chopper (1985) - Review, Star Cast, News, Photos|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2019-03-28}}</ref> He contested the [[2014 Lok Sabha elections]] from [[Birbhum]], West Bengal on BJP ticket against sitting MP and [[Cinema of West Bengal|Tollywood]] actress [[Satabdi Roy]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/402832/bjps-joy-banerjee-gives-satabdi.html |title=BJP's Joy Banerjee gives Satabdi a run for her money in Birbhum}}</ref>

